<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="715" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="50.[136,1059,472,684]" pageId="50" pageNumber="715">
COMMENTS: This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1992" box="[608,712,472,496]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudobironium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="715" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[608,712,472,496]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="715">P. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its colour pattern, body size and elytral punctation. It differs however in having much finer pronotal punctation, different length ratio of the antennomeres, in particular by the antennomere XI much longer than III, the microsculptured lateroposterior parts of the metaventrite and entire surface of the 1st abdominal sternite. The aedeagal characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl &amp; Liang Tang" authorityYear="2013" box="[854,969,598,622]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudobironium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="715" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stewarti">
<emphasis box="[854,969,598,622]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="715">P. stewarti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
suggest close relationships to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl &amp; Liang Tang" authorityYear="2013" box="[373,471,629,653]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudobironium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="715" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horaki">
<emphasis box="[373,471,629,653]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="715">P. horaki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1992" box="[525,630,629,653]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudobironium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="715" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[525,630,629,653]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="715">P. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs by the parameres conspicuously arcuate in lateral view and lacking apical lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
